1
00:00:23,160 --> 00:00:24,528
Maheen?

2
00:00:25,198 --> 00:00:26,659
Maheen!

3
00:00:30,190 --> 00:00:31,698
Maheen!

4
00:00:32,100 --> 00:00:33,158
Fajr!

5
00:00:33,194 --> 00:00:34,212
Fajr!

6
00:00:34,243 --> 00:00:37,464
Call the doctor! Maheen's not --

7
00:00:39,350 --> 00:00:41,233
What's up, Mum?

8
00:00:49,680 --> 00:00:51,089
Mum...?

9
00:00:52,770 --> 00:00:54,288
Mum...

10
00:00:56,090 --> 00:00:57,518
What?

11
00:01:02,830 --> 00:01:04,488
What happened?

12
00:01:59,260 --> 00:02:00,859
(Maheen...)

13
00:02:32,970 --> 00:02:34,359
(Maheen?)

14
00:02:37,970 --> 00:02:39,319
(Maheen...)

15
00:02:45,500 --> 00:02:48,141
What'd you nick just now?

16
00:02:49,281 --> 00:02:52,111
You complete blighter!

17
00:02:52,762 --> 00:02:56,433
I was just droppin' by to say hi.

18
00:02:57,110 --> 00:03:02,209
But you were sleeping as if you've got everything.

19
00:03:06,970 --> 00:03:08,658
Come here...

20
00:03:15,130 --> 00:03:16,888
What's the time?

21
00:03:17,188 --> 00:03:19,249
Almost midnight.

22
00:03:22,520 --> 00:03:24,469
You alright?

23
00:03:25,172 --> 00:03:28,443
'Course. That's why I was sleeping so peacefully.

24
00:03:28,743 --> 00:03:31,213
Girls... Blimey...

25
00:03:31,776 --> 00:03:33,933
Tell them

26
00:03:34,002 --> 00:03:36,743
They're getting what they've always wanted,

27
00:03:36,803 --> 00:03:39,624
And they sleep without a care!

28
00:03:40,354 --> 00:03:42,434
It's nothing like that.

29
00:03:42,620 --> 00:03:46,220
The doctor gave me a few meds after the bullet incident.

30
00:03:46,250 --> 00:03:48,968
They're a lot better at doing their job.

31
00:03:49,408 --> 00:03:52,459
But why are you here so late?

32
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:55,908
Just... Felt like comin'?

33
00:03:56,208 --> 00:04:02,318
Thought I'd sit with you a while... Have a chat...

34
00:04:02,418 --> 00:04:04,469
It'd ease me.

35
00:04:05,389 --> 00:04:07,204
You worried?

36
00:04:10,180 --> 00:04:11,468
Aye.

37
00:04:12,358 --> 00:04:13,999
Why?

38
00:04:17,770 --> 00:04:20,908
I just found out yesterday

39
00:04:22,210 --> 00:04:24,078
That Mum

40
00:04:24,718 --> 00:04:27,748
Was innocent all along.

41
00:04:28,430 --> 00:04:29,921
Whoa...

42
00:04:33,250 --> 00:04:35,758
Dad's shaken.

43
00:04:38,350 --> 00:04:41,548
Ashamed at everything he did.

44
00:04:42,870 --> 00:04:44,658
What good is it?

45
00:04:44,779 --> 00:04:47,870
She died a grieving woman.

46
00:04:48,073 --> 00:04:51,024
Not entirely Dad's fault though.

47
00:04:51,394 --> 00:04:53,875
What happened?

48
00:04:57,980 --> 00:05:00,228
I will... Someday...

49
00:05:02,660 --> 00:05:05,748
For now, I'm... Looking for him...

50
00:05:06,310 --> 00:05:07,898
I swear...

51
00:05:09,500 --> 00:05:12,039
I'll settle all scores.

52
00:05:13,169 --> 00:05:17,344
But you said he died with your Mum in the car crash?

53
00:05:19,739 --> 00:05:21,950
So he did, aye...

54
00:05:32,620 --> 00:05:34,938
But his kids...

55
00:05:37,360 --> 00:05:39,321
Gotta pay...

56
00:05:39,850 --> 00:05:42,447
For the sins of their father...

57
00:05:43,830 --> 00:05:45,968
Not fair, Jiya.

58
00:05:46,138 --> 00:05:48,388
What's their fault?

59
00:05:48,549 --> 00:05:50,250
That blighter's dead.

60
00:05:50,250 --> 00:05:54,260
You can do anything you want and he won't even stir in his grave.

61
00:05:55,520 --> 00:05:57,798
You don't know, but he will...

62
00:06:01,710 --> 00:06:05,762
I know his soul's lurking around here somewhere...

63
00:06:22,130 --> 00:06:23,988
Anyway...

64
00:06:25,818 --> 00:06:27,958
Have a good night's sleep...

65
00:06:28,048 --> 00:06:30,059
I'll be back.

66
00:06:32,890 --> 00:06:34,988
Take care.

67
00:06:36,018 --> 00:06:37,631
Won't you have a cuppa?

68
00:06:37,631 --> 00:06:39,063
No.

69
00:06:39,817 --> 00:06:43,608
I don't need a cuppa to stay awake now.

70
00:06:45,360 --> 00:06:46,710
Bye.

71
00:06:48,300 --> 00:06:49,778
Bye.

72
00:07:14,210 --> 00:07:15,758
Jiya!

73
00:07:19,940 --> 00:07:21,833
When'd you get in?

74
00:07:22,196 --> 00:07:24,521
Just a while ago?

75
00:07:24,633 --> 00:07:26,681
Sorry I didn't call...

76
00:07:26,721 --> 00:07:29,461
Just... Wanted to see her.

77
00:07:29,554 --> 00:07:32,834
Can't believe you're done so quickly!

78
00:07:32,895 --> 00:07:35,195
The blighter's turned in!

79
00:07:35,385 --> 00:07:37,896
Won't you have anything?

80
00:07:40,835 --> 00:07:42,976
Next time?

81
00:07:45,310 --> 00:07:48,498
I've got old ties to this place...

82
00:07:50,980 --> 00:07:53,538
I'll come knocking like I have a right...

83
00:07:54,930 --> 00:07:56,208
Bye.

84
00:08:17,520 --> 00:08:19,109
Hi partner!

85
00:08:19,159 --> 00:08:20,319
Hi.

86
00:08:20,399 --> 00:08:24,861
Lemme guess. She didn't take your call, so you thought you'd ask Fajr.

87
00:08:24,939 --> 00:08:26,250
No, mate...

88
00:08:26,310 --> 00:08:27,651
Worry not though

89
00:08:27,651 --> 00:08:31,901
The conditions have become completely concordant. Restrictions have been lifted.

90
00:08:31,901 --> 00:08:34,472
You can meet her easily.

91
00:08:34,510 --> 00:08:37,830
Speaking of which, why don't you two ever meet?

92
00:08:37,830 --> 00:08:38,788
Honestly

93
00:08:38,788 --> 00:08:42,618
I find it a sight to behold to see two lovers meet!

94
00:08:42,618 --> 00:08:44,009
See?

95
00:08:44,448 --> 00:08:46,788
Even you think I love her.

96
00:08:46,788 --> 00:08:49,368
I've always known it.

97
00:08:49,368 --> 00:08:51,808
She realised it a tad late.

98
00:08:51,898 --> 00:08:53,939
May I confide in you?

99
00:08:54,339 --> 00:08:55,639
Yes?

100
00:08:55,749 --> 00:08:59,250
But promise me it will stay between us.

101
00:08:59,291 --> 00:09:02,920
It will; you don't need my word for it.

102
00:09:03,760 --> 00:09:05,930
I don't love her.

103
00:09:06,200 --> 00:09:07,968
Ohhh!

104
00:09:08,120 --> 00:09:09,498
I swear

105
00:09:09,588 --> 00:09:11,898
I was just teasing her.

106
00:09:12,219 --> 00:09:14,330
She used to be so proud of herself,

107
00:09:14,390 --> 00:09:15,789
And now

108
00:09:15,922 --> 00:09:17,800
Look how I've shattered her ego!

109
00:09:17,800 --> 00:09:19,313
Put a sock in it.

110
00:09:19,313 --> 00:09:20,920
It's your ego that's been shattered.

111
00:09:20,920 --> 00:09:23,588
Springing off into the sky like that!

112
00:09:24,168 --> 00:09:26,470
I'm not joking, Fajr...

113
00:09:26,759 --> 00:09:28,559
I'm not joking either.

114
00:09:28,559 --> 00:09:31,949
I understand love better than both of you. Combined.

115
00:09:32,169 --> 00:09:34,190
That's why I feel guilty.

116
00:09:34,190 --> 00:09:35,160
Keep up with it.

117
00:09:35,160 --> 00:09:38,260
Keep feeling guilty for the rest of your life.

118
00:09:38,340 --> 00:09:41,619
Fajr, I'm so ashamed of myself and you don't even get it...

119
00:09:41,653 --> 00:09:47,534
I mean -- Her calling me and my turning back doesn't mean we love each other.

120
00:09:47,654 --> 00:09:51,363
Just think -- our quarrel's been resolved.

121
00:09:51,519 --> 00:09:55,454
Do you even know that she refused to wear the engagement ring?

122
00:09:55,454 --> 00:09:56,564
I know.

123
00:09:56,564 --> 00:09:58,394
The silly girl.

124
00:09:58,546 --> 00:10:00,730
What made her act so foolishly and unashamedly?

125
00:10:00,730 --> 00:10:02,728
Trapped me with herself.

126
00:10:02,788 --> 00:10:04,228
Trapped?

127
00:10:04,280 --> 00:10:05,791
Of course.

128
00:10:05,848 --> 00:10:09,539
Everyone's thinking we've got something going on.

129
00:10:09,598 --> 00:10:11,984
I'm almost dying of shame.

130
00:10:14,020 --> 00:10:19,079
How do I even begin to tell you I'd never even imagined I'd marry a country girl!

131
00:10:19,399 --> 00:10:21,624
Who told you to lie like that?

132
00:10:21,671 --> 00:10:23,652
I was lying back then.

133
00:10:23,870 --> 00:10:26,039
But now I'm telling the truth.

134
00:10:26,104 --> 00:10:27,719
100%.

135
00:10:29,480 --> 00:10:31,309
Upon reflection...

136
00:10:31,470 --> 00:10:34,801
I realised I shouldn't have flirted with her.

137
00:10:35,252 --> 00:10:37,616
After all, she's my cousin, mate.

138
00:10:37,692 --> 00:10:39,770
My Aunt's daughter.

139
00:10:40,861 --> 00:10:42,911
But I'm so stupid.

140
00:10:43,815 --> 00:10:45,330
I ended up making a mistake.

141
00:10:45,330 --> 00:10:47,535
Curse your filthy mouth!

142
00:10:47,598 --> 00:10:48,848
There!

143
00:10:48,929 --> 00:10:52,610
I knew you'd all curse me if you ever found out.

144
00:10:52,610 --> 00:10:54,738
But... Could <i>you</i> not say that?

145
00:10:54,798 --> 00:10:56,568
Are you going back?

146
00:10:56,618 --> 00:10:57,879
No.

147
00:10:58,050 --> 00:11:01,792
You're blowing the gaff on yourself and stayin' put here?

148
00:11:01,843 --> 00:11:04,671
I'll go, mate. In a few days.

149
00:11:06,520 --> 00:11:07,379
But

150
00:11:07,379 --> 00:11:09,469
First, I'll apologise to her.

151
00:11:09,649 --> 00:11:10,943
What?

152
00:11:11,129 --> 00:11:12,494
Aye.

153
00:11:12,649 --> 00:11:15,030
Today itself.

154
00:11:15,090 --> 00:11:17,931
Then don't tarry. You've got your chance.

